<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-02-02 11:05 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A8424 &Cx1f; tad-z
u l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-HEART-CANDY03-COX     02-02 0286
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HEART-CANDY03-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Bumper crop of Conversation Hearts at stores near you
 &HT;    By Pat Thomas
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   When the calendar page turns over to February and the groundhog
has been dragged from its den, it's time for another seasonal crop:
the conversation heart candy.
</P>
<P>
   For a few weeks every year, the NECCO (New England Confectionery
Co.) churns out millions of chalky, pastel heart-shaped lumps of
candy stamped with Valentine-themed words and sayings. The official
name is even a mouthful: Sweethearts brand Conversation Hearts.
</P>
<P>
   And each year, in addition to longtime favorites such as ``Be
Mine,'' ``My Man,'' ``Sweet Talk'' and ``Kiss Me,'' the company
adds what it considers trendy or thematic phrases.
</P>
<P>
   This year the company is taking its inspiration from popular
music and culture. The five somewhat eclectic musical phrases are:
``Love Me Tender,'' ``I Got U Babe,`` ``My Way,'' ``Let It Be'' and
``Walk On By,'' which pretty much seem to cover every potential
relationship stage from beginning to end.
</P>
<P>
   If you're not inclined to let the music do the talking, pick out
the new pop culture phrases: ``You Rock,'' ``Let's Do Lunch,'' ``I
Wonder'' and ``As If.'' There's also ``1-800 Cupid,'' although it
seems that ``10-10 CUPID'' would have been more timely, given the
incessant long-distance ad campaigns.
</P>
<P>
   Regardless of the sentiment (and how come I always seem to get a
handful of ``No Way''?), each candy is fat- and sodium-free. The
small hearts have about three calories each, the big ones, about
six.
</P>
<P>
   Pat Thomas writes for the Dayton Daily News, Dayton, Ohio.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-02-02-99 1105EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
