<P>
   KABAT-COLUMN _ WACO, Texas _ We all know how a certain scent can
conjure up a cornucopia of memories. The aroma of Avon face cream
always does it for me. Immediately, I'm 6 years old again, cuddled
up by my grandmother, listening to her bedtime stories on a
sleepover at her house. Certain places also can send us catapulting
through time and space on a wild, emotional ride of recollections.
This happened to me the other day. (Kabat, Waco Tribune-Herald)
MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TEEPEN-COLUMN _ (Teepen, Cox News Service) MOVED MONDAY.
</P>
<P>
   KLEINBERG-COLUMN _ If the Baltimore Orioles make good on their
intent to play in Cuba, likely in front of Fidel Castro himself,
the reception they get in Miami when they come to play the Marlins
June 7-9 will be beyond rude, perhaps violent. (Kleinberg, Cox News
Service.) MOVED MONDAY.
</P>
<P>
   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ GIBSONBURG, Ohio _ As I wander my classroom
looking for signs of writer's block, I can't help wondering what
makes eighth-graders tick and remembering what life was like when I
was their age. One obvious difference is the way they look.
(Schuett, Cox News Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   YOUNG-COLUMN _ WACO, Texas _ Much gets said about the revenue
potential of sporting venues, but that's a bake-sale charade. Even
at the big-time college level athletic departments are a chronic
revenue drain, and nothing drains resources like stadiums, their
empty seats gleaming in the sun. (Young, Waco Tribune-Herald)
MOVED.
