<P>
   COXNET-WHEELS 0129 _ A reminder really shouldn't be necessary,
but all the attention and praise being given the new Beetle seem to
warrant one: Volkswagen is still importing, and quite frequently
selling, the Jetta sedan. Fact is, the Jetta is the best-selling
Volkswagen in North America with 1998 sales totaling about 90,000,
prompting VW execs to call the Mexican-built car the leader here
among German sedans and the only six-cylinder European car
available for under $20,000. (DeVault, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   AT A GLANCE _ A look at the VW Jetta. (DeVault, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   THE MECHANIC _ Misdiagnosis of electrical repairs not only
contributes to the animosity between the consumer and the auto
repair industry but also costs millions of hours and dollars each
year in lost revenue. (Carter, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
