<HEADLINE>
SEATTLE NEWSPAPERS AMEND JOA AND EXTEND IT FOR 50 YEARS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 c.1999 Hearst Newspapers  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SEATTLE _ The Hearst Corp. and the Seattle Times Co. announced
Tuesday that they have agreed to amend their joint operating
agreement to permit the Seattle Times to switch from the afternoon
newspaper field and join Hearst's Post-Intelligencer in the morning
field. y+++ATH0
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
