<P>
   IOC-OLYMPICS
</P>
<P>
   IOCDRUGS _ LAUSANNE, Switzerland _ Barry McCaffrey wants to put
the fear of God into world-class athletes, advocating they be
subjected to possible drug testing 365 days a year. Test the
millionaire pros and the pixy gymnasts, alike. And check them both
for performance-enhancers and recreational drugs. McCaffrey,
director of the U.S. Office of National Drug Control Policy, led
the parade of government leaders Tuesday addressing the World
Conference on Doping in Sport (Fish, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
19
</P>
<P>
   w/IOC-SCANDAL _ LAUSANNE, Switzerland _ International Olympic
Committee officials said Tuesday the group will not pursue
allegations that an Australian official sought to influence two IOC
members with offers of $70,000 in grants, saying the offer was
within the bidding rules. Developing spot. (Roughton, Cox News
Service).
</P>
<P>
   IOCANDY _ LAUSANNE, Switzerland _ The head of the Australian
Olympic Committee had kind words for Andrew Young, but he failed to
retract his allegation that former Atlanta mayor and United Nations
ambassador dispensed U.S. government aid to African nations during
the bid process for the 1996 Olympics. Nor did John Coates offer
any details Tuesday to support his claims. (Fish, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
