television operator, and number three MediaOne announced Tuesday
they will swap several systems, including at some in metro Atlanta.
The swap involves 660,000 subscribers.
</P>
<P>
   Time Warner will get systems in Maine, California and Ohio;
MediaOne will get systems in Massachuysetts, New Hampshire and
Georgia. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
