<P>
   HOLSENDLOPH-COLUMN _ATLANTA _ The flowering of the information
age will change nearly everything we do in the next century, and
even alter the way we think about issues and weigh values. In the
unfolding new world, knowledge becomes the coin of the realm, a new
way to handle and expand time, and even a weapon in business and
economic warfare. Yes, what we used to call competition could
become undisguised combat. (Holsendolph, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   DELTA-FOOD _ ATLANTA _Delta passengers may notice something
missing in their Sky Deli bags starting Thursday: the sandwich.In a
cost-trimming move, the airline is taking the sandwiches out of the
bags on about 140 flights and replacing them with either cheese and
crackers or carrots and dip. Delta's also cutting back from full
meals to snacks in first-class on 80 flights and from snacks to
beverage service on another 160. That's still a minority of flights
on which food is served. (Staff, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) 10
</P>
