   MONEYTALK _ Feeling tired and a little bit guilty about all
those appeals for charitable causes? Now you can set up your own
charity. You can name it after yourself, take the tax deductions
right now for your contributions and decide at leisure just where
you want to send your donations. You can use it as a tool to get
your kids involved in good works, and you can leave it for them to
manage after you're gone _ a sort of immortality on the cheap.
Another benefit: Someone else will handle all the paperwork,
including tax reporting. (Ezell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
MOVED.
