<SLUG> BC-RICH-ADVISORY-NYT </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Editors, attention editorial page editors:
</P>
<P>
   Frank Rich, whose column has appeared on The New York Times'
Op-Ed page twice a week since January 1994, will write longer
articles for the page and become a regular contributor to The N.Y.
Times Magazine.
</P>
<P>
   Rich's twice-a-week columns, about 700 words long, will appear
until Feb. 13. He will then take a four-month leave to finish a
memoir for Random House and will return in June.
</P>
<P>
   Starting in June, he will write a 1,400-word opinion article for
the Op-Ed page every other Saturday. These columns will remain a
part of The N.Y. Times news service.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; The N.Y. Times News Service &LR;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
