<P>
   &UR; OPENING REMARKS FROM THE ``LATE SHOW with DAVID LETTERMAN'' &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``I want to take a second here to welcome Latrell Sprewell to
the New York Knicks. That's exactly what New York City needs --
another borderline psychotic with a hair-trigger temper.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Latrell Sprewell, as you know, had some trouble with his last
NBA team, with his last coach...but he's now a proud member of the
New York Knicks and already he's adjusting to life in New York City
--he's sleeping with Madonna.''
</P>
<P>
   ``It's different how different people celebrate -- when the
Atlanta Falcons score, they dance around; when I score, I just
leave 50 bucks on the dresser.''
</P>
<P>
   ``A guy in New Jersey lost his hand several years ago...and now
within the last couple of weeks, they have given him a brand new
hand. He is the first recipient of a successful hand transplant.
It's an amazing thing. And the guy was saying it's an incredible
experience. He says now he feels like he's having sex with a total
stranger.''
</P>
<P>
   ``According to Mayor Giuliani, more bad news for New York City.
Mayor Giuliani is now saying New York City has a pit bull problem.
I think he's right. I think we do have a serious pit bull problem.
Earlier today, I saw a pit bull using a wire coat hanger to break
into a Toyota Camry.''
</P>
<P>
   ``It's interesting. The pit bulls don't seem to be bothering
Mayor Giuliani, though. I guess it's just professional courtesy.''
</P>
<P>
   ``You folks happen to watch the Golden Globe Awards?...The
Golden Globe show, you may not have known this, was produced by
Dick Clark. Dick Clark is an amazing man. He's also producing the
impeachment.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I want to take a moment here to welcome Pope John Paul II to
the United States. Earlier this afternoon, he landed in St. Louis.
It's been quite a trip for this guy -- first, it was Mexico, today
it's St. Louis, and this weekend he'll be in Miami headlining the
big Super Bowl halftime show.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is very odd -- President Clinton is also in St. Louis. He
went there to talk to the Pope. He's trying to get the Pope to
endorse his very narrow definition of sex.''
</P>
<P>
   ``After Clinton met with Pope John Paul II, the Pope was
immediately subpoenaed by Henry Hyde.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Pope John Paul II, you probably know about this, he was in the
United States, he was in Missouri yesterday...Yesterday, [he said]
mass for 100,000 people. Unbelievable! It's like the largest indoor
crowd ever in the United States of America. The crowd was crazy.
They even had those big fat guys spelling out P-O-P-E.'''
</P>
<P>
   ``Mark McGwire was in St. Louis, he went to see the Pope and he
kissed the Pope's ring. Today -- listen to this -- the Pope
auctioned it off for $3.2 million dollars.''
</P>
<P>
   ``You feel like you're getting your money's worth out of the
impeachment so far? It's fun, isn't it? As your watching it,
remember one thing -- this is your tax dollars at work. The
interstates are crumbling, but we get this all day on TV.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Whenever the Senators want to ask a question, they have to
submit it in writing to Chief Justice Rehnquist. And, so far, the
single most often asked question written and submitted to Chief
Justice Rehnquist is, What's the deal with those stripes on your
robe?'''
</P>
<P>
   ``During the impeachment, whenever Ted Kennedy has a question,
he just writes it out on those cocktail napkins from Hooters.''
</P>
<P>
   ``You folks enjoying the impeachment? I don't think they know
what they're doing. For the second day in a row, the Senate met
behind closed doors for hours and hours and hours. Have no idea
what they're doing. Ted Kennedy came out three times for ice.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Over the weekend, Monica Lewinsky flies into Washington, D.C.,
and the House trial managers interview her for three hours in
a...hotel room. Here's the strategy on that deal: they're thinking,
well, maybe we're not going to be able to get Clinton out of
office, but we sure can make him jealous.''
</P>
