<HEADLINE>
RED SOX SIGN NO. 1 KOREAN AMATEUR   PITCHER 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By LARRY WHITESIDE  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOSTON _ Over the last two years, the Red Sox have expressed a
fondness for Korean pitchers. That sentiment has paid off with the
signing of Seung Jun Song, the No. 1 pick in the Korean amateur
draft.
</P>
<P>
   Song, 18, led Kyung Narm High School of Pusan to the national
championship in a 52-team tournament. The 6-foot-1-inch, 190-pound
righthander pitched nine innings of the final game, striking out
14. Song, who won three ``best pitcher'' awards in 1998, chose
Boston over several Korean professional teams.
</P>
<P>
   The Red Sox will get a look at Song this month in spring
training at Fort Myers, Fla. General manager Dan Duquette says he
like what he hears about Song, who was scouted and signed by Ray
Poitevint, Boston's executive director of international operations.
</P>
<P>
   ``Song is a workhorse who possesses a fastball in the 92-93
range with good movement,'' said Duquette in a statement. ``He has
shown at a very young age the potential to be a future front-line
big league pitcher.''
</P>
<P>
   Song is the third highly touted Korean to sign with Red Sox. Jin
Ho Cho rose from Single A Sarasota to Boston in less than a year.
He made four starts for the Sox in 1998, all in July (0-3, 18 2/3
IP, 8.20 ERA). Sun Woo Kim spent the entire 1998 season at
Sarasota, where he started 24 games (12-6, 4.82).
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The Sox still have two players awaiting arbitration, outfielder
Midre Cummings and pitcher John Wasdin.
</P>
<P>
   Cummings, 27, who made $250,000 last year, is seeking $750,000,
while the Sox have offered $600,000. His hearing will be Monday.
Cummings batted .283 in 67 games after being acquired on waivers
from Cincinnati.
</P>
<P>
   Wasdin, 26, is asking for $675,000, a raise of $448,000 over his
1998 salary. The Sox are offering $470,000. His hearing is
scheduled for Feb. 16. Wasdin appeared in 47 games in '98, eight as
a starter, and posted a 6-4 record with a 5.19 ERA.
</P>
</TEXT>
