   FREEZER-MURDER (St. Augustine, Texas) _ Marjorie Nugent, the
81-year-old widow of a millionaire banker in Carthage, Texas,
relied heavily upon Bernie Tiede, some 40 years her junior. From
the time he got up in the morning until bedtime at night, she
called him and gave him his marching orders. Finally on Nov. 19,
1996, Tiede snapped. The man confessed to shooting Nugent in the
back and stuffing her into her own freezer, where her body remained
for months. His lawyer says greed had nothing to do with it. By
ALLAN TURNER.
