<HEADER>
A9326 &Cx1f; tad-z
u a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FLA-PROFESSOR-SEX-COX     02-02 0517
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FLA-PROFESSOR-SEX-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Professor accused of making Honduran teen a sex slave
 &HT;    By Douglas Belkin
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   MIAMI _ A diminutive Honduran teen told a federal jury Tuesday
how Florida Atlantic University professor Marvin Hersh gave him
toys, clothes and money over three years in exchange for sex in
Honduras and in the suburban Boca Raton home he shared with Hersh.
</P>
<P>
   Speaking softly through an interpreter, the young man, now 18,
said he never wanted to have sex with the computer science
professor _ whom he called Mario _ but did so out of desperation.
</P>
<P>
   ``Because of poverty,'' he said. ``I wanted Mario to help my
family.''
</P>
<P>
   Hersh, 58, is on trial in federal court on charges of passport
fraud, alien smuggling and transporting a minor with the intent of
engaging in sexual activity. Prosecutors allege he seduced the teen
and two of his brothers with presents and money, then illegally
brought the boy to the United States in 1995 to use him as a sex
slave.
</P>
<P>
   Hersh's attorneys said outside of court that they believed
federal authorities coerced the young man into testifying against
Hersh by telling him that was the only way he would be allowed to
return to his native country. They will continue to cross-examine
the teen today.
</P>
<P>
   He testified Tuesday that in 1994 and 1995, Hersh came to
Honduras every three or four months and had sex with him. After
each encounter, he said, Hersh gave him presents, including a
plastic toy helicopter, clothes, and on one occasion, the Honduran
equivalent of $10.
</P>
<P>
   The teen, who has eight brothers and sisters, said he gave the
money to his mother.
</P>
<P>
   In 1995, Hersh gave him a fake passport and birth certificate
and brought him to the United States, the teen testified.
</P>
<P>
   The 5-foot-3-inch teen, who looks younger than his age, was
enrolled in the fourth grade at Whispering Pines Elementary School.
Hersh told him to tell anyone who asked that he was Hersh's son,
the teen said.
</P>
<P>
   In the meantime, the pair shared Hersh's bedroom.
</P>
<P>
   ``Did you have your own bedroom?'' Assistant United States
Attorney John C. McMillan asked.
</P>
<P>
   ``Yes, but I never used it,'' the boy answered.
</P>
<P>
   The boy initially denied that he had a sexual relationship with
Hersh when he was asked by police.
</P>
<P>
   ``I was ashamed,'' he said during the cross-examination. ``But I
am tired of lying. Everything Mario told me to say was a lie.''
</P>
<P>
   Hersh was suspended from his teaching post after his 1997
arrest. Since then, he has been in jail in Miami.
</P>
<P>
   The teen's mother testified Monday and several of his older
brothers are expected to take the stand later in the trial. Also
expected to testify is businessman Nelson ``Jay'' Buhler, who
accompanied Hersh to Honduras between 1994 and 1996 to have sex
with young boys, authorities say.
</P>
<P>
   Buhler has pleaded guilty to having sex with a minor and will
testify against Hersh as part of his plea bargain.
</P>
<P>
   Douglas Belkin writes for the Palm Beach Post, West Palm Beach,
Fla.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
